# Line-ending policy for this workshop.
#
# Every script here runs inside a LINUX Docker container via a bind mount
# (`.:/workspace`), so the host checkout MUST use LF line endings on every
# OS — including Windows. A single CRLF (\r) sneaking into a .sh file makes
# bash read `set -euo pipefail\r` and abort with "invalid option name", and
# CRLF in the Makefile or a shebang breaks them the same way.
#
# These rules override each attendee's local `git config core.autocrlf`
# setting. Whatever their Windows/Mac/Linux Git is configured to do, files
# come out of `git clone` with LF.

# Default: let Git detect text vs binary, and force LF on checkout everywhere.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Be explicit for the files that actually break under CRLF (self-documenting).
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.py        text eol=lf
Makefile    text eol=lf
Dockerfile  text eol=lf
*.yml       text eol=lf
*.yaml      text eol=lf
*.json      text eol=lf
*.md        text eol=lf
*.txt       text eol=lf
.gitignore  text eol=lf
